CatDescriptText: Mrs. Lovenia Harris, dress shop employee, 146 Robinson Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that President Eisenhower should invoke the Taft-Hartley Act in steel strike?" answer reads: "Yes, because it would allow the steelworkers to return to work."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lovenia Harris wearing light colored button earrings and dark coat, holding paper bag, standing in front of Beck Shoes, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
